#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:47
msgid "From Edge Angle"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:43
msgid ""
"If this button is enabled, edges will be split if their edge angle is "
"greater than the :guilabel:`Split Angle` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:45
msgid "The edge angle is the angle between the two faces which use that edge."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:46
msgid "If more than two faces use an edge, it is always split."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:47
msgid "If fewer than two faces use an edge, it is never split."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:50
msgid "Split Angle"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:50
msgid ""
"This is the angle above which edges will be split if the :guilabel:`From "
"Edge Angle` button is selected, from ``0`` (all edges are split) to ``180`` "
"(no edges are split). This performs the same action as the "
":menuselection:`Edge Specials --> Edge Split` menu item (:kbd:`ctrl-E`, in "
":guilabel:`Edit mode`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:54
msgid "From Marked As Sharp"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/modifiers/generate/edge_split.rst:53
msgid ""
"If this button is enabled, edges will be split if they are marked as sharp, "
"using the :menuselection:`Edge Specials --> Mark Sharp` menu item "
"(:kbd:`ctrl-E`, in :guilabel:`Edit mode`)."
msgstr ""

